{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 01:59:41.868093", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\n\nScope and Topology\n- Fabric: Multi-tier Clos (fat-tree) with EBGP everywhere (FRR).\n- Hosts: pc_0_0 (10.0.0.2/24 gw 10.0.0.1), pc_0_1 (10.0.1.2/24 gw 10.0.1.1).\n- Relevant routers: leaf_router_0_0 (AS 65200), leaf_router_0_1 (AS 65201), spine_router_0_0 (AS 65100), spine_router_0_1 (AS 65101), super_spine_router_0 (AS 65000).\n\nHigh-level Health Check\n- EBGP sessions across the fabric are established and stable:\n  - leaf_router_0_0: 8 neighbors, all Established, PfxRcd ≈ 31.\n  - leaf_router_0_1: 8 neighbors, all Established, PfxRcd ≈ 32.\n  - spine_router_0_0 and spine_router_0_1: 12 neighbors each, Established.\n  - super_spine_router_0: 32 neighbors, Established.\n- Routing tables on spines and super-spine contain full sets of /24 leaf prefixes as expected.\n\nDetected Anomaly\n- End-to-end connectivity between pc_0_0 and pc_0_1 fails:\n  - pc_0_0 -> pc_0_1 ping timed out.\n  - pc_0_1 -> pc_0_0 ping timed out.\n- Most other inter-host pings (to different destinations in the lab) appear healthy, indicating the issue is specific to the 10.0.0.x subnet (and hosts within 10.0.0.0/30).\n\nKey Findings and Evidence\n1) Misconfiguration on leaf_router_0_0 causing blackholing of a more-specific prefix:\n   - leaf_router_0_0 running-config:\n     - ip route 10.0.0.0/30 Null0\n     - address-family ipv4 unicast includes: network 10.0.0.0/24 and network 10.0.0.0/30\n   - leaf_router_0_0 RIB/FIB:\n     - S>* 10.0.0.0/30 unreachable (blackhole), weight 1\n     - C>* 10.0.0.0/24 is directly connected, eth8\n     - Due to longest-prefix-match, any traffic to 10.0.0.0–10.0.0.3 (including pc_0_0 at 10.0.0.2 and the default gateway 10.0.0.1) matches the /30 and is dropped to Null0 on leaf_router_0_0.\n   - BGP propagation of the more-specific /30:\n     - spine_router_0_0 BGP summary shows PfxRcd from AS 65200 = 2 (one extra prefix versus other leaves), consistent with receiving both /24 and /30 from leaf_router_0_0.\n     - super_spine_router_0 has BGP route for 10.0.0.0/30:\n       - B>* 10.0.0.0/30 via 172.16.0.1\n     - leaf_router_0_1 RIB contains:\n       - B>* 10.0.0.0/30 via 172.16.1.2\n     - This confirms the /30 is learned fabric-wide and preferred over the /24 due to specificity.\n\n2) Impacted traffic pattern:\n   - Any traffic destined to 10.0.0.0/30 (10.0.0.0–10.0.0.3) is attracted to leaf_router_0_0 via the /30 and blackholed at Null0.\n   - For pc_0_0 (10.0.0.2):\n     - Requests from pc_0_0 to off-subnet (e.g., to pc_0_1) can leave the leaf, but replies back to 10.0.0.2 hit the more-specific /30 at leaf_router_0_0 and are dropped.\n     - Requests from other hosts to 10.0.0.2 also follow the /30 to leaf_router_0_0 and are dropped before reaching the host.\n   - This explains bidirectional ping failures between pc_0_0 and pc_0_1.\n\n3) No systemic BGP/adjacency failure:\n   - All EBGP adjacencies are up, and other /24 reachability appears normal.\n   - The issue is a routing policy/content mismatch (route advertisement/installation) on a single leaf.\n\nFault Localization\n- Primary faulty device: leaf_router_0_0.\n- Secondary effect: All upstream devices (spine_router_0_0/0_1 and super_spine_router_0) correctly prefer and propagate the more-specific /30 learned from leaf_router_0_0, amplifying the blackhole impact network-wide.\n\nRoot Cause\n- Misconfiguration on leaf_router_0_0 introducing an overlapping, more-specific blackhole:\n  - Static route 10.0.0.0/30 to Null0 installed in the FIB.\n  - The same /30 is injected into BGP (network 10.0.0.0/30).\n  - Result: Longest-prefix match steers 10.0.0.0/30 traffic fabric-wide to leaf_router_0_0 where it is discarded, breaking reachability to pc_0_0 (10.0.0.2) and potentially any other IPs in that /30 range.\n\nAdditional Notes\n- pc_0_0 and pc_0_1 host configs are correct (IPs and default gateways).\n- The problem is not observed for other subnets because only leaf_router_0_0 advertises a conflicting more-specific blackhole.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 25945, "output_tokens": 5494, "total_tokens": 31439, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 25088}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 4224}}}
